ehicle|amphibious tank]]{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1088}}{{sfn|McKenna|2011|p=61}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=8}}\n* [[SU-76]] self-propelled gun{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1088}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=8}}\n* [[SU-100]] self-propelled guns in limited numbers.{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|pp=10, 65}}\n* [[SU-122]] self-propelled gun in limited numbers{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1088}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|pp=10, 65}}\n* [[T-34-85]] medium tank, from 1959{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1088}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=37}}\n* [[T-54/55|T-54]] main battle tanks,{{sfn|Dunstan|1985|p=40}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=8}} used from 1965{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=17}}\n* [[Type 59 tank|Type 59]] main battle tanks{{sfn|Dunstan|1985|p=40}}\n* [[Type 62]] [[light tank]]{{citation needed|date=December 2018}}\n* [[Type 63 anti-aircraft gun|Type 63]] anti-aircraft self-propelled systems\n* [[Type 63 (tank)|Type 63]] [[Amphibious vehicle|amphibious tank]]{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=35}}\n* [[ZSU-57-2]] anti-aircraft self-propelled systems{{sfn|Dunstan|1985|p=35}}\n* [[ZSU-23-4]] anti-aircraft self-propelled systems{{sfn|Dunstan|1985|p=40}}\n\n===Other armored vehicles===\n* [[BTR-40]] APC{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|pp=24-25}}\n* [[BTR-50]] APC{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=8}}\n* [[BTR-60]]PB APC{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=38}}\n* [[BTR-152]] APC{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=11}}\n* [[M3 Half-track]] and [[M8 Greyhound|M8 Light Armored Car]] - first NVA armored vehicles. Used to protect Air Bases in the North.{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=16}}\n* [[M113 armored personnel carrier]] - captured from the ARVN{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=10}}\n* [[T-54/T-55 operators and variants#Bridge-layer|MTU-20]] armored bridge-layer{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=40}}\n* [[Type 63 (armoured personnel carrier)|Type 63]] APC{{sfn|Conboy|1992|p=45}}{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=37}}\n\n===Support vehicles===\n{{More citations needed section|date=December 2018}}\n* [[AT-L]] light artillery tractor{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=41}}\n* AT-S and [[ATS-59]] medium artillery tractors{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=41}}<ref name=\"B&B54\"/>\n* [[Beijing BJ212]]<ref name=\"B&B53\">{{cite magazine|language=fr|title=Objectif Saigon !  2e partie : Surprise sur les Hauts Plateaux|magazine=Batailles & Blind\u00e9s|issue=53|date=February 2013|publisher=Carakt\u00e8re|issn=1765-0828|first=Albert|last=Grandolini|pages=8\u201321}}</ref>\n* [[Dnepr M-72]]\n* [[GAZ-AA]]\n* [[GAZ-MM]]\n* [[GAZ 46]] light amphibious car{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=50}}\n* [[GAZ-51]] truck (and Chinese copy){{sfn|Rottman 2011b|p=10}}\n* [[GAZ-63]] truck{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=25}}<ref name=\"Sherwood2004, p. 34\"/>\n* [[GAZ-64]] \n* [[GAZ-67]]\n* [[GAZ-69]]{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=16}}\n* [[IFA W 50]]<ref name=\"B&B53\"/>\n* [[KrAZ-255]] heavy truck{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=48}}\n* {{ill|Mazur D-350|pl}} artillery tractor{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|pp=47-48}}\n* [[MAZ-200|MAZ-502]] truck<ref name=\"Sherwood2004, p. 34\">{{cite book|title=Afterburner: Naval Aviators and the Vietnam War|first=John Darrell |last=Sherwood|date=May 2004|isbn=9780814798423|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=tCoUCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA34|publisher=[[New York University Press]]|page=34}}</ref>\n* [[M35 series 2\u00bd-ton 6x6 cargo truck|M35]] truck series (captured)<ref name=\"B&B54\"/>\n* [[M54 5-ton 6x6 truck|M54]] truck series (captured)<ref name=\"B&B54\"/>\n* [[M151 \u00bc-ton 4\u00d74 utility truck|M151 jeep]] (captured)<ref name=\"B&B53\"/>\n* [[PMZ-A-750]]\n* [[ZIS-150]] truck (and Chinese CA-10)<ref name=\"B&B54\">{{cite magazine|language=fr|title=Objectif Saigon ! 3e partie : La chute du r\u00e9gime sud-vietnamien|magazine=Batailles & Blind\u00e9s|issue=54|date=April 2013|publisher=Carakt\u00e8re|issn=1765-0828|first=Albert|last=Grandolini|pages=66\u201379}}</ref>\n* [[ZIS-5 (truck)|Ural ZIS-355M]] truck<ref name=\"Sherwood2004, p. 34\"/>\n* [[Ural-375]]\n* [[ZIL-130]] truck{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=41}}\n* [[ZiS-151|ZIL-151]] truck{{sfn|Toperczer|2001|p=28}}\n* [[ZIL-157|ZIL-157 and ZIL-157K]] trucks (and Chinese CA-30){{sfn|Toperczer|2001|p=34}}<ref name=\"B&B51\">{{cite magazine|language=fr|title=Objectif Saigon ! 1re partie :  Le renouveau nord-vietnamien|magazine=Batailles & Blind\u00e9s|issue=51|date=October 2012|publisher=Carakt\u00e8re|issn=1765-0828|first=Albert|last=Grandolini|pages=66\u201379}}</ref>\n* [[BAV 485|ZiS-485]] amphibious vehicle{{sfn|Grandolini|1998|p=49}}<ref name=\"B&B54\"/>\n\n===Naval craft===\n* [[Shantou-class gunboat|Swatow-class gunboats]]{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1321}}\n* [[P 4-class torpedo boat|P4 and P6 torpedo boats]]{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=1321}}\n* Countless civilian-type [[sampan]]s - mainly used for smuggling supplies and weapons{{sfn|Tucker|2011|p=705}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[NLF and PAVN strategy, organization and structure]]\n* [[NLF and PAVN logistics and equipment]]\n* [[NLF and PAVN battle tactics]]\n* [[Weapons of the Laotian Civil War]]\n* [[Weapons of the Cambodian Civil War]]\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations and notes ===\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book|title=US Army AH-1 Cobra Units in Vietnam|series=Combat Aircraft 41|first=Jonathan|last= Bernstein |date=25 Sep 2003|isbn=9781841766065|publisher=Osprey Publishing|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=The NVA and Viet Cong|series=Elite 38|first=Kenneth |last=Conboy |date=30 Jan 1992|isbn=9781855321625|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=cyvDCwAAQBAJ|publisher=[[Osprey Publishing]]|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Armour of the Vietnam Wars|series=Vanguard 84|first= Simon|last= Dunstan |date=24 Jan 1985|publisher=Osprey Publishing|isbn=9780850455854|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Small Arms of the Vietnam War: A Photographic Study|first1=Dale A. |last1=Dye|first2= Tom |last2=Laemlein|isbn=9780986195518|publisher=Warriors Publishing Group|date=18 Aug 2015|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KR5ZCgAAQBAJ|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Personal firepower|first=Edward Clinton|last=Ezell|publisher=Bantam Books|year=1988|series=The Illustrated history of the Vietnam War 15|oclc=1036801376|url=https://archive.org/de